Leuven J Corthout
den ue van 15 deser ontf & oock de ƒ 300 wisselgelt van den bode
wallenus volgens de quittantie aen hem gegeven, ick ben seer bedroeft
te sien ue clachte, dogh wat willen wijdoen den rouw & droef heytis

den ue van 17 deser geeft mij eenigh achterdencken over de
schepen van hul, on dat thomas chaman segh hij allen
is gecomen die packen in heeft hebbe de convoyers huin tt
hul gelaeten, soo sal de swarigheyt, soo groot niet wesen
als wel verlies van tijt maer souden die op soe achter uyt
geseylt sijn, soo soude sulcksx seer qualijck gedan wel
wat daer van is & waer die andere schepen sijn verbleven
ben ick in groot verlangen te verstaen, bedancke ue voor het

hul hude maze binnen was dogh dat de convoyers de schepen met

sghanan, sijn d'andere tot hul blijven liggen, soo vertrouwe de

Londen Jan Kent
19 meirt
f sence my last of 16 cur rec yours of 28 pastt the rott
convoj is arrived from hull & no cloths ships butt thomas
seaman, how & where the rest is exspect to heare from you
this a greeet disapointement now if they should be lef att hull
& will not come for Amst with that convoy so take out N10 8 26
but of costhulst & reship for Amst with what you can gett
readdy of the lest ordered goods, what I ordered 2 curs to have 2 pack
of cloth there with did not contradict the formar pack onley, to maked
that up then or there about to them patt, so loose no time to gett
somer cloth, for Amst further the sp. clothes resting of my orders
of 19 Janu. have said must be to N1a 6 inclosee are the patt.
as I would have them there, or there about lovelyer or better mixt
& liveley if possible & so make up that pack & send for Rott or
first convoy that way Amst. or ostend refervinge you to my
latten ren
these patt are for N4 & 6 on the patt of 19 jauu lett mee
have 4 a 5 clothes to these patt from 7, 8,9 to 10 p of
each prise so mething the rest of the pack to the white & other
grayes as the patt N1, 2 u 3 & 5
